title: Google Pixel Watch 4 Review | What's Actually Changed?
description: Reviewing Google's Pixel Watch 4 (41mm model) after two weeks of testing as my full-time smartwatch. You've got a few upgrades for this 2025 model, including a (slight) battery increase and improved haptics. But is the Google Pixel Watch 4 one of the best WearOS smartwatches for you?  Well, I'm certainly a fan of that WearOS 6 setup. Notification support is as smooth as ever, while you've got impressive app support. You can live stream your Nest doorbell or control your smart home, so anyone embracing the ecosystem will get the most from Google's Pixel Watch 4.  Performance on the whole is fine, with the new W5 Gen 2 running the show. Sometimes you'll see a wee stumble or an app will take a while to load. And this smartwatch once again suffers from a less-than-significant battery life. The Pixel Watch 4 simply can't compete with some rival wearables, which I discuss in this review.  Still, if you're after a good looking curvy smartwatch with lots of Google support, you could do worse. Would you be tempted by the Pixel Watch 4? Let us know below!
